TITLE: CDC investigating more than 100 cases of unexplained hepatitis in children, including 5 deaths
SUMMARY: The US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention said Friday that it's investigating 109 cases of severe and unexplained hepatitis in children in 25 states and territories that may be linked to a worldwide outbreak.

TITLE: GOP still favored in midterms, despite possible overturning of Roe v. Wade
SUMMARY: The national political environment has favored Republicans since last fall. And it has only gotten worse for Democrats in the months since as inflation has skyrocketed and President Joe Biden's approval rating has dropped.

TITLE: Kraft Heinz has an extremely unique solution for supply chain backups
SUMMARY: Kraft Heinz is using the metaverse to help get Lunchables, Velveeta and ketchup onto shelves faster.

TITLE: Netflix could turn things around by allying with an old foe
SUMMARY: Netflix is still reeling from its stock plunge last month after losing subscribers for the first time in more than a decade.

Car enthusiasts help teen who lost dream car
Nine hospitalized after Texas authorities find dozens of undocumented workers in semi trailer
SUMMARY: Nine people were treated for dehydration and scores of others fled the scene when authorities discovered up to 100 undocumented workers in the trailer of a broken-down semi in rural Texas, officials said Friday.

TITLE: Tennessee governor signs bill criminalizing mail-in abortion drugs
SUMMARY: Tennessee Governor Bill Lee signed a bill Thursday criminalizing abortion-inducing drugs that are provided via mail.

TITLE: Second body recovered after three children went missing in Mississippi River
SUMMARY: The body of a 14-year-old girl was found in the Mississippi River, the second body recovered after three children went missing in the water last month, according to the New Orleans mayor.

TITLE: In Pennsylvania, McCormick campaign keeps up attacks over Oz's Turkish ties
SUMMARY: Republican Senate candidate Dave McCormick has honed in on a closing message in the final days before the May 17 Pennsylvania primary: questioning the patriotic loyalties of his main primary opponent, Mehmet Oz.

TITLE: Judge dismisses Trump lawsuit against Twitter over ban
SUMMARY: A federal judge in San Francisco has dismissed former President Donald Trump's lawsuit against Twitter that sought to reinstate his banned account on the platform, according to a court filing.

TITLE: Who is Brad Raffensperger, Georgia's Republican secretary of state?
SUMMARY: Georgia Secretary of State Brad Raffensperger is being swept into another sensitive political matter, the latest in a series of headline-grabbing incidents for an official whose day-to-day duties typically render the position obscure.

TITLE: A double-dip recession might be hard for the Fed to avoid
SUMMARY: The Federal Reserve finally seems prepared to whip inflation. The last time the Fed faced surging prices like this, it jacked up interest rates and the US economy endured multiple slowdowns. Do Americans need to fear a repeat of the early 1980s?
